      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/community/2013/09/04/muse-of-the-revolution</guid>
      <description>I had two New Year’s resolutions in 2011: to read Leo Tolstoy’s Anna Karenina and Marcel Proust’s In Search of Lost Time. Anna was completed by Jan. 25 – just when our lives turned into a 24-hour TV marathon tuned to Cairo’s Tahrir Square as the world watched a dictator fall in 18 short days.</description>
