      <author>Amal Hanano</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/articles/2013/02/22/syrian-stories-armed-with-a-mic-and-camera</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/syria/articles/2013/02/22/syrian-stories-armed-with-a-mic-and-camera</guid>
      <description>On April 25, 2011, a man held up a video camera in Deraa. He was not an experienced videographer and he did not have a tripod.He stood in front of a group of Syrian army soldiers with tanks and filmed them shooting their machine guns towards civilian targets. Each time he watched the clip on his laptop, he noticed the footage was shaky due to his trembling hand, so he would go back to his exposed vantage point to film once more.</description>
